<!--   GRADING  -->
<h3>Grading</h3>
Your grade will be determined based on the following factors:
<ul>
  <li>Completion of project milestones on time (design, MATLAB coding,
testing)</li>
  <li>Correctness and quality of your work, i.e.,</li>
  <ul>
    <li>does your code function correctly,</li>
    <li>how well the code is designed/written/tested,</li>
    <li>how well it is documented,</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Understanding of basic concepts underlying the algorithms</li>
  <li>Your ability to evaluate your results and the presentation
quality of
your
project reports.</li>
</ul>
<p>There will be two parts to the class:</p>
<ul>
  <li>The first 5  weeks or so: weekly assignments  using MATLAB: worth approximately 40% of your grade, with the lowest scoring assignment dropped. </li>
  <li>The second 5 weeks: project proposals,  project progress reports, project presentation in class, and final project report: worth approximately 60% of your grade </li>
</ul>
<hr>
<!--    ASSIGNMENTS......
<h3>Assignments</h3>
Your grade will be based on progress in the class as measured by your
assignment
work. Assignments must be submitted by the due date and time, there
will
be no exceptions (please do not ask the TA or instructor about
exceptions.
If your assignment is late, it will not be graded).&nbsp; If you are
not
finished working on your assignment by the time it is due, please
submit
whatever you have.<br>
<br>
Completed assignments should be uploaded to the EEE 175A dropbox under
the folder for that Assignment (i.e.,
Assignment1, Assignment2, etc). For more details on dropboxes please
consult the <a
 href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/computing/nt/dropboxes/dropboxes_faq.php">ICS
FAQ on dropboxes</a>.<br>
<p>The first 7 assignments are each worth 10 points. Your lowest
scoring
assignment will be discarded and your top 6 scoring assignments used to
calculate your total score (so your maximum score is 60 points). In
this
way you can miss one assignment without penalty (however please be
aware
that assignments are incremental in that some of the later assignments
will build on code you wrote in earlier assignments).
</p>
<p>Your final project will be worth 40 points (for a total possible
score
of 100 points in the class). You must submit an acceptable final
project
to pass the class.
</p>
<p>Intermediate grades will be issued during midterm week. This is the
grade
that you would have gotten if the class ended at that point: it is
intended
to provide you with feedback on how you are doing in the class at that
time. It does not necessarily reflect your final grade, i.e., your
final
grade may be higher or lower depending on your performance in the
second
part of the quarter.
</p>
